main event: Two separate sightings of a silver-colored object over the Woodbridge-Manassas, Virginia area, lasting over three hours
interesting points: The object was seen at different locations during the sightings, indicating it was moving.
Both observations were beyond the horizon, suggesting the object was at a high altitude.
The object had a blinking red light on top that blinked three times, paused, and then blinked three times again.
The second sighting, which was 10 miles away from the first, occurred three hours later and had an identical description of the object.
The report mentions that the observers, which included a civilian and military personnel, stated the object was definitely not an aircraft due to its motion.
